Acceptance criteria

This packet is acceptable only if all of the following are true:

1. The pack pipeline is no longer an oversized mixed-responsibility path.
2. Canonical writer behavior is structurally clearer.
3. Experimental profile logic is more explicitly bounded.
4. Layout planning is separated from byte emission.
5. Dictionary/auxiliary structure handling is more isolated and reviewable.
6. Tests demonstrate no semantic drift in canonical and representative experimental writer behavior.
